dogs.name: Casemiro
dogs.description: Casemiro has really struggled in kennels is looking for a home with a secure garden where she can pootle about and live out her retirement years. Domino would like to be the only pet in the home and will require further socialisation when out and about with other dogs. Domino can share her home with children aged 12 years and older. Domino has previously been left for a few hours but would need this to be built up in a gradual way in her new home until she is settled and comfortable. Domino will happily hop into the car so will be able to go on adventures further afield.

dogs.name: Sasha
dogs.description: Sasha is a mixed breed puppy, approximately 2 months old, and currently weighs 7 pounds. Sweet Potato is a bubbly, energetic puppy seeking an active family of his own! As with any puppy, he will need patience and understanding as he navigates and learn about the world around him! He'll benefit from reward-based training as he learns about potty training and foundation manners. Although he is small now, he will grow up to be a medium to large sized dog with moderate to high energy levels. He will also benefit from continued socialization to other dogs, people, sights and sounds!

dogs.name: Oliver
dogs.description: OIiver is a 1 year-old mixed breed who weighs 21 lbs. He is an unbelievably sweet and loyal boy! He was surrendered to the shelter when his owner could no longer care for him. Oliver loves nothing more than sitting on laps and getting all the attention. He also enjoys playing with other dogs and sniffing around the play yard. If you're looking for a loving companion who wants to cuddle all day long, then Oliver is the dog for you!

dogs.name: Olivia
dogs.description: Olivia looks like a tough cookie but she is soft and gooey in the center. If you want a friend who is happy to go on a low key walk or stay on the couch and snuggle with you, she's your girl! Given the choice, Olivia prefers to hang out with people rather than dogs. She doesn't mind other calm pups but can be a bit nervous around them. For those walks she likes so much, she is easy to leash and likes to sniff. Olivia is sweet treat who is all ready to be packed up, taken home, and enjoyed.

dogs.name: Sprouts
dogs.description: He looks like a tough cookie but she is soft and gooey in the center. If you want a friend who is happy to go on a low key walk or stay on the couch and snuggle with you, she's your girl! Given the choice, Sprouts prefers to hang out with people rather than dogs. She doesn't mind other calm pups but can be a bit nervous around them. For those walks she likes so much, she is easy to leash and likes to sniff. He is sweet treat who is all ready to be packed up, taken home, and enjoyed.

dogs.name: Alpha
dogs.description: Alpha is an energetic 1 year old Australian Shepherd who is looking for an active family. While at CHA, Alpha has enjoyed play sessions with other dogs in the fenced play yard and spending time with staff and volunteers. If you are looking for active playful dog, possibly even a running buddy, come meet Alpha today!

dogs.name: Scooter
dogs.description: Scooter is a big, goofy puppy ready to steal your heart! This handsome boy isn't just good looking, he's also smart and food motivated! He already knows sit and would benefit from continued rewards-based training to gain confidence. He's a sensitive guy and can get startled by loud noises and things in the environment, but seeks a lot of comfort from trusted people. Mikey was exuberant when greeting another dog and may do best with other social dogs similar in size. Mikey is a large mixed breed, likely a Pointer mix, approximately 6 months old and currently weighs 52lbs. He still has growing to do, so he'll weigh more as he matures.

dogs.name: Coco
dogs.description: Coco is an adorable dude seeking a family to show him the world is a fun place to explore. It seems that Coco lived a somewhat sheltered life before arriving at our shelter partner, Gigi's. He is uncertain about novel objects in his environment, however he is quick to explore and be brave. Coco lets his happy-go-lucky side show pretty quickly with is goofy personality and playful nature. When meeting other dogs, he immediately pops into play bows and he acts like a puppy even though he's an adult dog. This smarty pants already knows Sit and Shake, and will enjoy continuing reward-based training with his future family! If you're seeking a playful dog that looks to his people for reassurance then Coco may be your guy! He's a medium sized mixed breed, approximately three years young, and currently weighs 43 pounds

dogs.name: Mac
dogs.description: Mac n Cheese is a silly, slightly timid girl searching for a new family after ending up at one of Gigi's rural partner shelters as a stray. This sensitive girl is shy at first but will seek comfort from people once she is comfortable. She is sure to entertain with her goofy zoomies and adorable play bows. Mac n Cheese is eager to please and already knows sit- she would benefit from continued reward-based training in her new home. She was more interested in getting her sniffs in than interacting with another dog- she may prefer to be an only dog or do fine with a calmer dog that will give her space. Mac n Cheese is a medium mixed breed dog, approximately 3 years old and weighs 35lbs.

dogs.name: Mariano
dogs.description: Mariano is looking for a home with understanding owners who are familiar with this breed or similar. He is quite a nervous boy and will need his new adopters around all the time initially to help him settle in, build his confidence and cope being left on his own. He could live with another dog who will be a positive role model to show him the doggy ropes. He could live with children 14 years and older, who are confident around large, exuberant dogs and will enjoy training Rocket and help him build his confidence. He would need a fully enclosed, private garden as he isn't fully housetrained yet. He would need to attend our Dog School classes.

dogs.name: Brabacika
dogs.description: I have found this little pup on the street and took her to the vet for vaccines and chip. She is very bubbly and friendly, always ready for cuddles. I can't keep her because I already have a dog which is not very kind to another dogs, unfortunately.
